    <task id="LOCAL-00017" summary="Script intro patch. The org $80B923 directive was 2 bytes too early. $B923 is the BRA instruction at the end of copyUnitFirstName, not the start of copyUnitSurname. The actual surname function starts at $B925, which is what the game's JSR $B925 (at $80:B8FE) targets. After patching, $B925 contained the bank byte of the JSL target ($80), which the CPU interpreted as&#10;   a BRA $04 — sliding into the NOPped-out shared loop and crashing. Changed org $80B923 → org $80B925, extended the first patch to cover the 2 extra BRA bytes, and adjusted NOP padding.">
